children.subject: Who would be the point of contact in order to obtain the EECS chair's signature for the CPF? Having trouble finding out that information, thanks!

history.content:
Dear good people,

Proposals for fall 2017 DeCals are due to the Senate by Tuesday July 11th, 2017.  That means that they --filled out and with the chair's signature-- should be brought to the EE or CS chair's assistant for the chair's signature with enough lead time that a facilitator could give time for them to sign (a few days perhaps) and then pick up the form and walk it to the Senate offices in Stephens Hall.  Before then you will need to visit staff in 379 Soda for CS DeCals and in 205 Cory for EE or EECS Decals to get information about room scheduling and enrollment management.  For aspiring student facilitators who won't be in town over the summer, you can absolutely do this during spring semester.

More information regarding opportunities and expectations/requirements can be found here:

http://academic-senate.berkeley.edu/committees/coci/sfc

and also here www.decal.org 

EECS (EE and CS) don't have specific earlier deadlines as some departments do but we would appreciate being able to honor campus deadlines.

All the best,

Michael-David
